LDK Seniors’ Living is building Australia’s most innovative seniors living
villages, delivered through a genuine continuum of care, in world-class
vibrant communities, that will truly be worthy of our seniors.

Our vision is to create the most loved seniors’ communities in Australia,
through our ‘one move’ promise. At LDK, our three core values that we live and
breathe by every day, are Love, Decency and Kindness. Every aspect of our
business has only one thing in mind – our residents.

Our five-star retirement living villages include a wide range of food and
beverage offerings from fine dining to cafés. Premium hospitality service
forms a key part of why our residents love living at LDK and project
management will play crucial role in the future of this ongoing success.

Are you a strategic thinker, a skilled collaborator, a star problem solver?
Come join us at LDK where you’ll kick start your Project Manager role with us
as the pivotal leader of our Food Management Project!

** Position Purpose: **

In your project management career at LDK you will have full accountability for
Projects from planning, approval, scoping through to delivery and
implementation. Acting as the focal point for our Operations team, you will be
set up for success to deliver in spades!

** Position Accountabilities: **

  * Responsible for end-to-end delivery of projects in line with established LDK project management methodology. 
  * Develop and manage project plans, engaging with key stakeholders and staff. 
  * Define work packages and supervise delivery of technical, stakeholder engagement and marketing specialists. 
  * Maintain project risk and manage risk mitigation activities. 
  * Develop and implement effective stakeholder engagement and communication strategies. 
  * Ensuring projects are delivered to schedule, budget and quality standards. 
  * Progress reporting and maintenance of project logs. 

** Skills and experience required: **

  * 5 years of Project Management experience. 
  * High level communication and engagement skills with a proven track record of partnering with diverse stakeholders in a national organisation. 
  * Knowledge of and experience in applying project management methods. 
  * Strong consultative and interpersonal skills with success in developing and coordinating risk/issue mitigation strategies across complex, multi-tiered structures. 
  * Proven ability to successfully manage complex projects using a formal project management approach. 
  * Demonstrated prioritisation, planning and problem-solving skills. 

** Highly desirable: **

  * Relevant project management qualifications. 
  * Qualifications or experience in Prince2 methodology 
  * Experience managing software development projects. 

